article_title: China Taps Alibaba, Tencent for Private-Bank Program
article_text:
BEIJING—Two of China's largest Internet companies are among Beijing's choices to set up five private banks, as the government enlists private capital to shake up the state-dominated banking sector.

Alibaba Group Holding Ltd. and Tencent Holdings Ltd. both will take part in the program, which a Chinese regulator said Tuesday would establish private banks on a trial basis in the big cities of Tianjin and Shanghai, as well as in...
